    "Since we use ranking loss to train the model, we only need to ensure that there is a difference in the ranking between different cases.",
    "Their score can be {1,-1,-2,-3} or {3,2,1,0}, both are acceptable.",
    "In this paper, for convenience, we choose {1,-1,-2,-3}.",
    "Here, R(Not Pass & Match) > R(Pass & Not Match), it is because Match is more difficult than Pass in tool-using tasks.",
    "After analyzing 4,443 seed training data from ToolBench, the distribution of these data on two metrics is shown in Table 24: Statistics on the distribution of reward metrics for 4,443 seed training data."
